ITLE`\n  - `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY`\n- Must complete before finalize runs\n- Required: This is the only mandatory workflow\n\n**3. finalize Workflow** (Phase 3)\n- Post-main cleanup, runs on **both success and failure**\n- Receives outcome context via environment variables:\n  - `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - \"succeeded\" or \"failed\"\n  - `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - ID of the main workflow run\n- Optional: skipped if absent\n- Implementation location: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 901-924\n\n### Code Implementation Files\n\n**Core Host Workflow Execution:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - `Runner` struct executes named workflows\n  - `Run()` / `RunWithID()` - execute main workflow\n  - `RunNamed()` - execute any named workflow\n  - `RunListTasksWorkflow()` - special handler for list-tasks with deduplication\n  \n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - `Executor` struct executes individual steps\n  - `executeScript()` - runs shell commands\n  - `executeWorkflow()` - dispatches container workflows via gRPC\n  - `executeAgent()` - runs agent on host\n  - `waitForRun()` - polls until container run completes\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop management\n  - `Loop` struct manages continuous orchestration\n  - `NewPhaseLoop()` - creates three-phase loop with list-tasks, main, finalize functions\n  - `runPhased()` - implements the phase orchestration (lines 174-271)\n  - `pickTaskFromPhase()` - selects next open task with deduplication (lines 309-351)\n  - Task deduplication prevents rapid reassignment within configurable timeout (default 5 min)\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` - Task data structures\n  - `Task` struct with JSONL marshaling\n  - `TaskStatus` constants: `open`, `closed`, `in-progress`\n  - `IsOpen()` - checks if task is assignable\n  - `ParseTasksJSONL()` - parses JSONL task output\n  - `ReadListTasksOutput()` - reads most recent .out file from host run\n\n### Environment Variables for Host Workflows\n\nAll host steps receive:\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - Project directory path\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - Where step output should be written\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - Previous step's output file path\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - Current task ID (main phase and later)\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` - Host run ID\n- Plus any wire output mappings\n\nFinalize phase additionally receives:\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - \"succeeded\" or \"failed\"\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - Container run ID from main phase\n\n### Step Types in Host Workflows\n\nHost workflows support three step types (defined in `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n1. **script** (`run` key) - Execute shell command\n2. **agent** (`prompt` key) - Invoke coding agent on host\n3. **workflow** (`workflow_name` key) - Dispatch container workflow, wait for completion\n   - Optional `prompt_step` config to override which step's output to use as prompt\n\n**Validation Rule:** `workflow_name` steps only allowed in host workflows (not container workflows) - enforced at parse time in `ValidateLocation()`\n\n### Actual Implementation in Cloche\n\n**Default host.cloche** (created by `cloche init`):\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` - Actual project's orchestration workflow with three workflows:\n  - `list-tasks` - runs `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh`\n  - `main` - multi-step: claim-task → prepare-prompt → develop → merge → cleanup\n  - `finalize` - runs close-task script\n\n**Associated Scripts:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh` - Lists available tasks\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/claim-task.sh` - Claims a task\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` - Generates prompt from task data\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/merge-to-main.sh` - Merges completed work\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/cleanup-run.sh` - Cleanup after run\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/close-task.sh` - Closes task in tracker\n\n### DSL Parser\n\n**Parser function:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n- `ParseAllForHost()` at line 43 -