{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V6BmiY1jhBC334aEg2EyLA","type":"tool_result","content":"   259→## Workflow Locations\n   260→\n   261→**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   262→via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   263→\n   264→**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   265→Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   266→dispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   267→execute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   268→fixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   269→\n   270→A single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n   271→uses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n   272→\n   273→| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n   274→|-------|--------------|---------|\n   275→| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n   276→| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n   277→| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n   278→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1b08d49b-02d1-4c4d-80e7-fef14e91a7aa","uuid":"bc049212-a2a0-46aa-b4e9-8ddd4db391a2","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\nexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\nfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n\nA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\nuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n\n| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n|-------|--------------|---------|\n| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n","numLines":20,"startLine":259,"totalLines":664}}}
